n for hybridization. However, despite this, the suggested hybrid SARIMAX- BiLSTM model was superior to the basic SARIMAX model in all four states based on the two metrics used, namely RMSE and MAE. This is evidenced by the reduction in RMSE values from 0.87 mm (Kerala) to 2.22 mm (Himachal Pradesh). The seeming contradiction between white noise residual diagnostics and observed hybrid improvement is seen as proof that the BiLSTM finds low-level non-linear structure in the SARIMAX residuals. This structure includes non-linear conditional dependencies and regime-switching patterns linked to the start and end of the monsoon, which are real but too subtle to show up as statistically significant linear autocorrelation at a monthly time scale.",
