 within a month, gets rid of the short-lived extreme events that cause the most forecast errors, and cuts the training dataset down to about 450 samples, which is too few to fully use the power of deep learning architectures. At a daily resolution, SARIMAX residuals would likely have a lot more non-linear structure, which would give the BiLSTM component a better learning signal and probably lead to bigger improvements over the statistical baseline. Incorporation of large-scale climate indices. The outcomes of this study, especially Kerala's consistently elevated RMSE, necessitate the incorporation of extensive oceanic and atmospheric teleconnection indices as supplementary exogenous variables. The El Ni˜no Southern Oscillation (ENSO), measured by the Ni˜no 3.4 sea surface temperature index, and the Indian",
