ement for the SARIMAX-BiLSTM hybrid, especially at daily time scales. There, you'll have enough training data to let the Transformer do its thing. Spatial modelling. In this study, each state was boiled down to a single, spatially averaged time series. This approach ignores all the local differences, glossing over the fact that rainfall isn't uniform within state boundaries. There's a lot more nuance, especially in bigger states like Rajasthan and Maharashtra-districts often vary widely. Future research needs to tackle this spatial complexity head-on. Models like convolutional LSTM (ConvLSTM) and graph neural networks can handle both space and time, letting us see how rainfall patterns evolve and interact across the landscape. Uncertainty quantification. Every model in this study churned out point forecasts without saying a word about uncertainty. That's",
